# IDs From Display Names

Story and World Forge authored objects get **stable snake_case ids derived from their display title/name**, not hand-typed opaque codes.

## Convention

- Input: human title — `Go Get the flowers`
- Output id: `go_get_the_flowers` via `engine::slugify_id` / `unique_slugify_id` (`include/engine/core/id_slug.h`)
- Lowercase, non-alphanumerics → `_`, collapse repeats, trim edges
- On collision, append `_2`, `_3`, …

## Editor UX

- Create flows prioritize **display name / title / summary**
- Show derived id as a preview; do not require a separate id field for normal authoring
- Keep free-text id only for advanced override when already supported
- Lookups still use dropdowns of existing ids (see `lookup-fields-dropdowns.mdc`)

## Examples

```text
❌ BAD: Force authors to invent `qggtf01` while also typing the title
✅ GOOD: Title "Go Get the flowers" → id `go_get_the_flowers` (unique_slugify if taken)
```
